OL,7,FMandy, whose name we have changed to
OL,8,Fprotect her identity, was raped when
OL,9,Fshe was a teenager and is one of those
OL,10,Fcalling for the register.
OL,12,FShe says: "I see them and I walk the
OL,13,Fother way because I don't want to walk
OL,14,Fpast them. Even if it happened thirty
OL,15,Fyears ago they should be on a register
OL,16,Fand it should be public. We need to
OL,17,Fknow who they are."
OL,19,FThe lack of Guernsey's public register
OL,20,Fhas led to some taking matters into
OL,21,Ftheir own hands.
